cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a model based on overcomplete denoising autoencoders to recover loss to followup information in healthcare. This involves working with high volume data and modeling highly non-linear relations and complex interactions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a novel model for data recovery. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the paper involves developing a model for healthcare data analysis. Additionally, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with data privacy and security concerns in healthcare.
